items.content:
Hi Kyle,


Acknowledging receipt of this ticket. I will QA the pixel and update you as soon as I'm done.


Thanks, Heidi
Thank you so much!

Heres the link they sent me https://tagassistant.google.com/#/?id=GTM-TQ8S3F4&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolverine.com%2FUS%2Fen%2Fhome%3Fgtm_debug%3D1706791694367&source=TAG_MANAGER&gtm_auth=scqkXA5nl3wYvjpgHKo5Kw&gtm_preview=env-566

Got it, working on this now!


Heidi

Hi Kyle,


Checking the GTM debug link they sent, I am only seeing the Pixel Base Code installed:

So, as I click through the site, I am only seeing PageView. For example, when landing on a product detail page, I would expect to see a ViewContent event, but that event does not fire:

As a next step, they should go in and set up the event triggers. The instructions from our TikTok GTM Template will help. 


I also see that they have events from Events Builder embedded in the site:

You cannot use events from both Event Builder and GTM. The client should go in and delete those Event Builder events, instructions to do so are attached.


Please let me know if there are further questions!


Thanks, Heidi

items.content:
Hi Heidi, 


They are having a few issues deleting events in TTAM.
Are you able to identify which events were set up with the event builder? I know their dev team has been working on the pixel, so if you could go look again, that would be awesome. :)
Here is a link to their TTAM https://ads.tiktok.com/i18n/dashboard?aadvid=6923271637450113026

Hi Kyle,


Please ask the client to disregard this direction for now. I need to raise the issue to product and find out why that error message displays even when the client didn't go through Event Builder. Apologies!


Heidi
Thank you for the update!

Hi Kyle, 


Checking in on this thread. The other instructions I sent still stand. So let me know if they make changes and I will take another look!


Thanks, Heidi
Great, thank you! I have sent over the instructions and will check back in later this week.
[Status Update] Made a follow-up with CSM on 2/6. The client has only set up pixel base code and is moving forward with implementing full funnel. I will follow up on Monday 2/12.

Hi Heidi, 


Here is the updated pixel link if you can please audit. https://tagassistant.google.com/#/?id=GTM-TQ8S3F4&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolverine.com%2FUS%2Fen%2Fhome%3Fgtm_debug%3D1707906822366&source=TAG_MANAGER&gtm_auth=scqkXA5nl3wYvjpgHKo5Kw&gtm_preview=env-566


Thank you so much!

Hi Kyle,


Thank you for your patience, I missed the reply here! I checked the Google Tag Assistant link, except for CompletePayment, which I would need a test credit card or coupon code to check. So far I see:


PageView fires when the landing page loads:

ViewContent also fires and parameters look good:

AddToCart fires as expected and most parameters are reporting:

Except for the 'value' parameters where there looks to be a formatting error:

the client should check the way they have added the price or other value, and make sure they are not passing any currency symbols, special characters, or commas. Specifically, I'm seeing for 'quantity' the value:

quantity: "1|1":

which could definitely be the cause.


If they are able to provide a test login, I can check CompletePayment. 


Thanks, Heidi
This is super useful, thank you!
Good morning! I sent exactly what you sent me and this was a question that came up. What would you say to this?

Hi Kyle, this might be legit. Let me check with my team and get back to you.


Heidi
Great, thank you!

Hi Kyle, no, you cannot have a pipe or any other character in the 'quantity' value as the data type must be a number. Per the documentation:

This would definitely cause the 'value' to report as 'undefined' as you see in the above screenshot.


Thanks, Heidi
Thank you so much!

Hi Kyle, looks like the client is still experiencing issues with CompletePayment. Keeping this open for now and I will investigate again.


Thanks, Heidi
